CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1945, pg. 3 reads: "First Anniversary Celebration - the Pittsburgh Interracial Action Council celebrated its first anniversary, at ....Henry, with an elaborate banquet, Monday evening.  Over 200 guests attended the celebration.  At the left is Broadus Mitchell, director of the American Economic Association, who was principal speaker...Harris Photo.."
TitMainTitle: Broadus Mitchell, director of the American Economic Association, speaking at microphone at head banquet table, in interior with egg and dart moldings, for the Pittsburgh Interracial Action Council anniversary celebration
